<task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="post-air-gapped-install" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"><title>On an air-gapped machine</title><shortdesc/><prolog><author type="creator" translate="no">Eamonn Smith &lt;eamonn.smith@puppet.com&gt;</author></prolog><taskbody><prereq><p><note type="note">Make sure your air-gapped machine  meets the system requirements for installing and running <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/remediate"/>, and that you have received your license. </note></p></prereq><steps><step><cmd>On a machine with internet connectivity, download the <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/remediate"/>  docker compose file.</cmd></step><step><cmd>To export the <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/remediate"/>  container images, create the <codeph translate="no">remediate.tar.gz</codeph> file by running the following command:</cmd><info><p><codeblock translate="no" xml:space="preserve">docker compose run remediate export</codeblock></p><p><note type="remember">You must export to a machine running the same operating system. The file size is approximately 1 GB and may take time to export.</note></p></info></step><step><cmd>Transfer the <codeph translate="no">remediate.tar.gz</codeph> file and the <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/remediate"/>  docker compose file to the air-gapped machine.</cmd></step><step><cmd>To import the <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/remediate"/>  container images into the local Docker registry, run the following command:</cmd><info><p><codeblock translate="no" xml:space="preserve">docker compose run remediate import -f &lt;tar file&gt;</codeblock></p></info></step><step><cmd>To check that all the container images have imported, run this command: </cmd><info><p><codeblock translate="no" xml:space="preserve">docker ps</codeblock></p><p>The list of running containers is:</p><p><codeblock translate="no" xml:space="preserve">CONTAINER ID        IMAGE                                             COMMAND                  CREATED             STATUS                   PORTS                NAMES
